CNCP v1 24566
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#7542: inconsistent behaviour of `whitespace: 'condense'` handling if second element text is an interpolated var",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:25:08.564224+00:00",
  "text": "inconsistent behaviour of `whitespace: 'condense'` handling if second element text is an interpolated var\n\n### Vue version\r\n\r\n3.2.45\r\n\r\n### Link to minimal reproduction\r\n\r\nhttps://sfc.vuejs.org/#\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\n\r\nAs described by [Evan's words](https://github.com/vuejs/vue/issues/9208#issuecomment-450012518), indenting the subsequent element will add a space between text content of the two nodes\r\n\r\n```vue\r\n<template>\r\n  <span>Foo</span>\r\n  <span>\r\n    Bar\r\n  </span>\r\n</template>\r\n<!-- outputs Foo Bar -->\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen the second element's content is a variable (not hardcoded text) the template compiler does not recognize it as text and removes the space.\r\n\r\n```vue\r\n<script setup>\r\nconst bar = ref('Bar')\r\n</script>\r\n\r\n<template>\r\n  <span>Foo</span>\r\n  <span>\r\n    {{ bar }}\r\n  </span>\r\n</template>\r\n<!-- expect to output Foo Bar, but outputs FooBar -->\r\n```\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n\r\nIt outputs `Foo Bar` in the first example as expected and `FooBar` in the second which is not expected.\r\n\r\n### System Info\r\n\r\n```shell\r\nN/A it's vue's SFC playground env, which uses `whitespace: 'condense'` (default), the only requirement to reproduce\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### Any additional comments?\r\n\r\nThe behaviour is inconsistent, and it's especially problematic when you're dealing with dynamic content — a classic real-world scenario is looping through a key/value object and outputting a definition list of things for example.\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Known workarounds\r\n- Setting compilers `whitespace: 'preserve'` would work, but is not an option for me because it [breaks a lot of other rather critical stuff](https://github.com/vuejs/core/issues/5153#issuecomment-1381701932)\r\n- Manually Adding `&nbsp;` HTML entity, but damn this whole `condense` thing is not aligned with the last 20 years of HTML (that I can remember of) and I would rather not go down that rabbit hole.",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":lady_beetle:  bug"
  ],
